INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'b08db77b-415a-4dd9-9d02-b4d960e85e6e',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Ansible Fact Caching — Remote State, Redis Backends, and Locking Gaps$escape$,
  $escape$Ansible doesn't persist state like Terraform, but fact caching fills the gap. By configuring a caching backend in `ansible.cfg`, gathered facts survive across playbook runs — enabling cross-playbook fact sharing and cutting SSH round-trips on large inventories.

Redis is the standard backend for distributed teams. Set `fact_caching = redis`, `fact_caching_connection = redis://localhost:6379/0`, and `fact_caching_timeout = 86400` under `[defaults]`. With `gathering = smart`, Ansible skips collection entirely when cached data is fresh — a measurable speed-up on inventories with hundreds of hosts.

Ansible has no native state locking. Concurrent playbook runs against the same inventory risk cache corruption or task interleaving. AWX/Ansible Automation Platform handles this through its built-in job scheduler and resource locking. For standalone Ansible, wrap invocations with `flock -n /tmp/ansible.lock ansible-playbook site.yml` or set `serial: 1` at the play level to cap parallelism to one host batch at a time.

Inspect cached facts with `ansible -m cache -a 'dump'` or query Redis directly via `redis-cli`. Flush stale entries mid-play using `meta: clear_facts`, which resets the in-memory cache for the current play without touching the persistent backend.$escape$,
  $escape$# ansible.cfg — configure remote fact cache backend
[defaults]
gathering             = smart
fact_caching          = redis
fact_caching_connection = redis://localhost:6379/0
fact_caching_timeout  = 86400

[inventory]
cache             = True
cache_plugin      = jsonfile
cache_connection  = /tmp/ansible_inventory_cache
cache_timeout     = 3600

# External lock prevents concurrent playbook runs from corrupting cache
flock -n /tmp/ansible.lock \
  ansible-playbook site.yml -i inventory/prod$escape$,
